OL,4,Cafter killer recommended for open
OL,5,Cprison
OL,7,F"There was no evidence to suggest that
OL,8,FMr Bell might abscond if he were to be
OL,9,Fplaced in an open prison."
OL,11,FThe Parole Board said in the summary
OL,12,Fthat no significant concerns had been
OL,13,Fraised about Bell's behaviour and
OL,14,Foutlined the steps he had taken to
OL,15,Faddress his problems within the prison.
OL,17,FIt said: "The panel heard that he had
OL,18,Fmade good progress, completing all the
OL,19,Frequirements of the prison."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G7/8
